<!-- BROKER REVIEW REQUIRED before push: confirm this wording with EXIT Realty Central. -->
<LegalLayout
  title="Fair Housing"
  description="EXIT Realty fair housing policy and Equal Housing Opportunity commitment."
  lastUpdated="June 11, 2026"
  showEhoMark={true}
>
  <p>
      EXIT Realty Corp. International (“EXIT”) is committed to supporting the guidelines of the U.S.
      Fair Housing Act (Title VIII of the Civil Rights Act of 1968), as amended, which prohibits
      discrimination in the sale, rental, and financing of housing transactions because of race, color,
      religion, sex, handicap, familial status, or national origin. State and local governments may
      impose additional requirements. Each EXIT Realty office is required to comply with all laws, rules,
      and regulations pertaining to the real estate industry – including the Fair Housing Act. EXIT is a
      real estate franchise company. Each EXIT office is independently owned and operated.
  </p>

  <h2>My commitment</h2>
  <p>
      Every client gets the same professional service — full stop. Federal law prohibits housing
      discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex, disability, familial status, and national
      origin, and New York State and New York City extend protection further — including lawful source
      of income, age, sexual orientation, gender identity, marital status, and military status. I follow
      the letter and the spirit of those laws.
  </p>

  <h2>What this means when we work together</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>I show you every option that fits the criteria and budget you give me. Nothing gets filtered by who lives where.</li>
    <li>My guides describe housing stock, prices, transit, and trade-offs. Where you belong is your decision — my job is accurate information, not opinions about people.</li>
    <li>For questions like school performance, I'll point you to official public sources — like the NYC DOE's zone finder — so you can apply your own standards. I don't characterize neighborhoods by who lives in them.</li>
    <li>Housing vouchers (Section 8, CityFHEPS, HASA, and similar) are lawful income in New York. Source-of-income discrimination is illegal, and I don't participate in it.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If you believe you've experienced discrimination</h2>
  <p>
      You can file a complaint with
      <a href="https://www.hud.gov/fairhousing" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> HUD</a>,
      the
      <a href="https://dhr.ny.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> New York State Division of Human Rights</a>,
      or the
      <a href="https://www.nyc.gov/cchr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"> NYC Commission on Human Rights</a>.
      If something felt wrong in a transaction I was part of, I want to know — <a href={withBase('/contact')}>contact me</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Official notices</h2>
  <p>
    <a href={SITE.nysFairHousingNoticeUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      New York State Housing and Anti-Discrimination Notice (PDF)
    </a>
    {' '}·{' '}
    <a href={withBase('/legal/sop')}>Standard Operating Procedures</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
